Requirement for pontis Bridge Management System:
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT1 The pontis System shall provide licensing agencies with an up-to-date tool for bridge management, including data management, condition assessment, model development, needs analysis, reporting, and interaction with other agency systems.
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT2 The pontis System shall be the next generation of the Pontis product, currently deployed in more than 45 agencies in the U.S. and abroad.
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT3 The pontis System shall support a range of new functionality, including import and export of data in eXstensible Markup Language based on TransXML schema being developed through National Cooperative Highway Research Program Project, XML Schemas for Exchange of Transportation Data.
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT4 The pontis System shall improved approaches to modeling bridge needs through incorporation of research results from NCHRP, Multiple-Objective Optimization for Bridge Management Systems.
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT5 The pontis System shall improved user interfaces for bridge-level analysis and project planning.
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT6 The pontis System shall support for multiple asset types.
PURPOSE OF THE PRODUCT7 The pontis System shall provide seamless support to its licensees for potential changes in the National Bridge Inventory coding standards. 

Specific goal The pontis System shall provide the AASHTO member agencies and licensees with a readily-accessible, robust repository for bridge information, technically correct capabilities to perform bridge management tasks of all types, a technologically up-to-date development foundation, streamlined, simpler application and deployment mechanisms, a flexible, customizable application which users can extend to solve agency, reservation of significant agency investments in BMS generally and Pontis specifically, including expenditures of time, money, training and other agency resource.

Development Technology Constraints1 The pontis System shall be developed using Microsoft technologies. DER
Development Technology Constraints2 The pontis System shall be a Microsoft NET application consisting of a combination of stand-alone, thin client, and back-end server applications. AND
Development Technology Constraints3 The pontis System shall maximize the use of third-party code libraries, whether fee-licensed or open-source, to minimize original development costs to the greatest extent possible. 

General Solution Constraints1 The pontis System shall take full advantage of web display capabilities including, in particular, screen real estate management to minimize scrolling, paging and tabbing. 
General Solution Constraints2 The pontis System shall support its existing relational databases of Sybase Adaptive Server Anywhere, Oracle, and Microsoft SQL Server as the database for its information repository.
General Solution Constraints3 The pontis System shall integrate its bridge information  with a more general asset management database structure which may incorporate other types of assets such as sign structures, high-mast towers, walls, pavements, or buildings.
General Solution Constraints4 The pontis System shall be a GIS-aware application that must operate properly with an GIS of agency technology whether ESRI, Intergraph, Open GIS, or others. 
General Solution Constraints5 The pontis System shall observe industry standard protocols in this regard and avoid vendor specific implementation approaches. 

ASSUMPTIONS1 The pontis System shall not assume a uniform operating environment and must accommodate both disconnected and connected users.
ASSUMPTIONS2 The pontis System shall maintain consistency with the existing deployed ver4 application.
ASSUMPTIONS3 The pontis System shall incorporate its design with any Federal NBI changes that may arise during the design and development period.
ASSUMPTIONS4 The pontis System shall use technology that the member agencies of AASHTO can deploy. 
ASSUMPTIONS5 The pontis System shall be designed as a deployed/installed application in agencies.
ASSUMPTIONS6 The pontis System shall not be designed as a hosted application, although it may well operate perfectly acceptably in a hosted configuration, such as a Citrix environment. 
ASSUMPTIONS7 The pontis System shall be a licensed product, which AASHTO will maintain ownership over, and which will be deployed with license protection to certain licensees such as consultants, international agencies, and academic institutions. 
ASSUMPTIONS8 The pontis System shall interact effectively and properly with the other BRIDGEWare products.
ASSUMPTIONS9 The pontis System shall provide two-way XML data exchange with TransXML schema once it is established. 
ASSUMPTIONS10 The pontis System shall provide well-defined and documented access to selected product functionality and data for third-party developers. 

